The following text was copied from http://www.praxiom.org/iso-intro.html (see our paragraph 1 and 4) to http://www.mediklinhealthcare.com/profile_credentials.htm (see your first paragraph):
“ISO 9001 applies to all types of organizations. It can help both product and service oriented organizations achieve standards of quality that are recognized and respected throughout the world. ISO 9001:2000 has replaced the old ISO 9001 1994 standard. In addition, the old ISO 9002:1994 and ISO 9003:1994 quality standards have been discontinued. They are now obsolete.”

NOTE: we emailed a copyright infringement notice to Mediklin on November 8, 2011. No response.
